==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recitation
<hw>Rec`i*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧s`⟦icr⟧*t⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>recitatio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧citation</ets>. See <er>Recite</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of reciting; rehearsal; repetition of words or
sentences.</def> <rj><au>Hammond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The delivery before an audience of something
committed to memory, especially as an elocutionary exhibition; also,
that which is so delivered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Colleges and Schools)</fld> <def>The rehearsal of a
lesson by pupils before their instructor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recitative</ent>⟦br⟧
